    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>An extremely hard variety of basalt that is jet black in color with a faint steak of mottled white; was often used as a touchstone for metallurgists.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
